<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="988" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d988">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.24/93</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The First Secretary of the British Embassy</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hayter</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chief of the Division of Near Eastern
                                Affairs</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Alling</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">3475/13/43</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-22">December 22,
                                1943</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Alling</hi>: Many thanks for your letter
                            of December 15th about military supplies to Saudi Arabia. I agree that
                            the modifications you propose are in accordance with our
                            discussions.</p>
                        <p>We have had confirmation from London that the authorities there are in
                            agreement with the conclusions reached and are issuing the necessary
                            instructions.</p>
                        <p>Yours sincerely,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>W. G. <hi rend="smallcaps">Hayter</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>